WEBVTT

1
00:00:19.728 --> 00:00:23.232
<i>This is the night</i>

2
00:00:23.398 --> 00:00:26.902
<i>It's a beautiful night</i>

3
00:00:27.069 --> 00:00:33.075
<i>And they call it Bella notte</i>

4
00:00:34.201 --> 00:00:37.162
<i>Look at the skies</i>

5
00:00:37.329 --> 00:00:41.041
<i>They have stars in their eyes</i>

6
00:00:41.208 --> 00:00:47.339
<i>On this lovely Bella notte</i>

7
00:00:47.923 --> 00:00:51.051
<i>So take the love</i>

8
00:00:51.218 --> 00:00:54.555
<i>Of your loved one</i>

9
00:00:54.721 --> 00:01:00.602
<i>You'll need it about this time</i>

10
00:01:01.395 --> 00:01:07.025
<i>To keep from falling like a star</i>

11
00:01:07.192 --> 00:01:11.238
<i>When you make that dizzy climb</i>

12
00:01:11.405 --> 00:01:16.910
<i>For this is the night</i>

13
00:01:17.077 --> 00:01:22.207
<i>And the heavens are right</i>

14
00:01:22.833 --> 00:01:25.794
<i>On this lovely</i>

15
00:01:25.961 --> 00:01:30.841
<i>Bella notte</i>

16
00:01:32.634 --> 00:01:35.345
<i>On this lovely</i>

17
00:01:35.512 --> 00:01:41.685
<i>Bella notte</i>

18
00:02:05.292 --> 00:02:10.339
<i>Silent as a snowflake in the night</i>

19
00:02:10.505 --> 00:02:15.135
<i>Holy is the spirit of this night</i>

20
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:20.098
<i>All the world is calm and peaceful</i>

21
00:02:20.265 --> 00:02:24.936
<i>All the world is bright and joyful</i>

22
00:02:25.103 --> 00:02:29.066
<i>Spirit of love</i>

23
00:02:29.232 --> 00:02:34.863
<i>And child of peace</i>

24
00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:39.409
<i>Love unending</i>

25
00:02:39.576 --> 00:02:45.248
<i>That shall not cease</i>

26
00:02:45.415 --> 00:02:50.587
<i>Peace, my children</i>

27
00:02:50.754 --> 00:02:55.592
<i>Of good will</i>

28
00:02:56.301 --> 00:02:58.512
<i>Peace, my children</i>

29
00:02:58.679 --> 00:03:04.685
<i>Peace, be still</i>

30
00:03:07.896 --> 00:03:09.231
It's for you, darling.

31
00:03:09.398 --> 00:03:10.732
Merry Christmas.

32
00:03:10.899 --> 00:03:12.776
Oh, Jim, dear.

33
00:03:12.943 --> 00:03:15.153
It's the one I was admiring, isn't it?

34
00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:17.197
Trimmed with ribbons?

35
00:03:17.364 --> 00:03:20.909
Well, it has a ribbon.

36
00:03:22.703 --> 00:03:25.831
Oh, how sweet.

37
00:03:25.997 --> 00:03:28.500
- You like her, darling?
- Oh, I love her.

38
00:03:32.504 --> 00:03:35.632
What a perfectly beautiful little lady.

39
00:03:46.351 --> 00:03:48.478
Come on, Lady. Over here.

40
00:03:50.522 --> 00:03:52.149
That's a girl.

41
00:03:53.859 --> 00:03:57.487
There, now.
A nice little bed for you.

42
00:03:57.654 --> 00:04:00.782
But Jim, dear, are you sure
she'll be warm enough?

43
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:04.161
Why, of course, darling.
She'll be snug as a bug in a...

44
00:04:05.454 --> 00:04:07.247
Almost forgot something.

45
00:04:08.373 --> 00:04:10.250
There.

46
00:04:10.417 --> 00:04:11.668
Good night, Lady.

47
00:04:11.835 --> 00:04:13.503
Now, now, don't worry, darling.

48
00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:15.422
She'll go right to sleep.

49
00:04:17.674 --> 00:04:19.009
No, no, Lady.

50
00:04:21.386 --> 00:04:24.931
This is where you belong, right here.

51
00:04:42.949 --> 00:04:45.869
Aw, look. She's lonesome.

52
00:04:46.036 --> 00:04:48.955
Don't you think maybe...?
Just for tonight?

53
00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:52.000
Now, darling, if we're going
to show her who's master,

54
00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:54.294
we must be firm
from the very beginning.

55
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:31.373
Lady!

56
00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:32.707
Stop that now!

57
00:05:32.874 --> 00:05:34.292
Stop it!

58
00:05:52.269 --> 00:05:55.522
Lady! Quiet, now. You hear me?

59
00:05:55.689 --> 00:05:57.274
Back to bed!

60
00:05:57.774 --> 00:05:59.192
Quick, now.

61
00:06:00.485 --> 00:06:02.779
Not one more sound.

62
00:07:00.378 --> 00:07:01.546
Jim, dear.

63
00:07:09.262 --> 00:07:10.805
Aw, Jim.

64
00:07:10.972 --> 00:07:12.182
What?

65
00:07:19.981 --> 00:07:21.816
Oh, all right.

66
00:07:22.984 --> 00:07:25.695
But remember, just for tonight.

67
00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:10.156
All right, Lady. All right.

68
00:08:10.323 --> 00:08:13.034
I'm up. I'm up, Lady. I...

69
00:08:13.201 --> 00:08:15.537
Oh, no!

70
00:08:15.704 --> 00:08:17.288
What's wrong, Jim? What is it?

71
00:08:17.455 --> 00:08:20.250
Can't you explain to Lady about Sundays?

72
00:09:32.614 --> 00:09:35.575
Have you noticed, darling,
since we've had Lady,

73
00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:39.412
we see less and less
of those disturbing headlines?

74
00:09:39.579 --> 00:09:43.666
Yes, I just don't know
how we ever got along without her.

75
00:09:44.417 --> 00:09:47.295
Say, she must be about six months old.

76
00:09:47.462 --> 00:09:49.380
We'd better be getting her a Licence.

77
00:10:04.479 --> 00:10:05.897
Hope it fits.

78
00:10:07.107 --> 00:10:09.609
My, but it does look nice.

79
00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:11.069
So grown up.

80
00:10:11.236 --> 00:10:13.863
Won't Jock and Trusty be surprised?

81
00:10:29.921 --> 00:10:33.091
<i>Four steps straight
and then to the left</i>

82
00:10:33.258 --> 00:10:37.011
<i>And right to the place
where I marked it</i>

83
00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:41.057
<i>With a bonnie, bonnie bone
that I buried for me own</i>

84
00:10:41.224 --> 00:10:45.228
<i>In my bonnie, bonnie bank
in the backyard</i>

85
00:10:46.729 --> 00:10:48.982
That's a grand sight.

86
00:10:49.149 --> 00:10:50.275
Jock!

87
00:10:52.152 --> 00:10:53.987
Oh, Jock!

88
00:10:59.826 --> 00:11:01.452
Hello, Jock.

89
00:11:01.619 --> 00:11:04.414
Oh! Oh, it's you, lassie.

90
00:11:04.581 --> 00:11:06.541
Notice anything different?

91
00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:09.752
You've had a bath?

92
00:11:09.919 --> 00:11:11.421
No, not that.

93
00:11:11.588 --> 00:11:13.756
You've had your nails clipped?

94
00:11:15.133 --> 00:11:16.885
Guess again.

95
00:11:17.343 --> 00:11:20.805
Well, I wouldn't a-be a-knowin'.

96
00:11:24.017 --> 00:11:25.602
Why, lassie.

97
00:11:25.768 --> 00:11:27.645
A bonnie new collar.

98
00:11:27.812 --> 00:11:30.023
- Do you like it?
- Aye.

99
00:11:31.900 --> 00:11:34.277
It must be very expensive.

100
00:11:35.153 --> 00:11:37.488
- Have you shown it to Trusty yet?
- No.

101
00:11:37.655 --> 00:11:40.200
We'd best go at once.

102
00:11:40.366 --> 00:11:43.620
You know how sensitive
he is about these things.

103
00:12:03.806 --> 00:12:05.516
He's dreaming.

104
00:12:05.683 --> 00:12:06.768
Aye.

105
00:12:06.935 --> 00:12:09.187
Dreamin' of those bonnie bygone days

106
00:12:09.354 --> 00:12:12.482
when he and his grandfather
were trackin' criminals

107
00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:14.150
through the swamps.

108
00:12:14.317 --> 00:12:17.153
- They were?
- But that was before...

109
00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:19.739
Before what?

110
00:12:20.323 --> 00:12:23.284
'Tis time you knew the truth, lassie.

111
00:12:23.451 --> 00:12:26.079
It shouldn't have happened to a dog.

112
00:12:26.246 --> 00:12:28.790
But, well...

113
00:12:28.957 --> 00:12:31.876
Trusty has lost his sense of smell.

114
00:12:33.211 --> 00:12:34.796
- No!
- Aye.

115
00:12:35.505 --> 00:12:38.258
But we must never let on
that we know, lassie.

116
00:12:39.259 --> 00:12:42.220
It would break his poor heart.

117
00:12:50.186 --> 00:12:52.981
Which way did he go?
Which way did he go?

118
00:12:53.147 --> 00:12:56.067
- Go?
- Yeah, big fella.

119
00:12:56.234 --> 00:12:57.986
About six-foot-two.

120
00:12:59.028 --> 00:13:00.446
No, three.

121
00:13:00.613 --> 00:13:03.366
Wore a striped suit. No collar.

122
00:13:04.367 --> 00:13:07.662
Why, Miss Lady.

123
00:13:07.829 --> 00:13:09.998
You have a collar.

124
00:13:11.332 --> 00:13:12.542
And a Licence.

125
00:13:12.709 --> 00:13:14.502
My, my.

126
00:13:14.669 --> 00:13:17.839
- How time does fly.
- Aye.

127
00:13:18.006 --> 00:13:20.383
It seems only yesterday
she was cuttin' her teeth

128
00:13:20.550 --> 00:13:22.260
on Jim Dear's slippers,

129
00:13:22.427 --> 00:13:26.514
and now there she is, a full-grown lady.

130
00:13:26.681 --> 00:13:31.144
Wearin' the greatest Honour
man can bestow.

131
00:13:31.311 --> 00:13:33.771
The badge of faith and respectability.

132
00:13:35.315 --> 00:13:37.692
That's right, Miss Lady.

133
00:13:37.859 --> 00:13:41.863
As my grandpappy,
Old Reliable, used to say...

134
00:13:42.030 --> 00:13:45.533
I don't recollect if I've ever
mentioned Old Reliable before.

135
00:13:45.700 --> 00:13:47.952
Aye, you have, laddie.

136
00:13:48.119 --> 00:13:49.954
Oh, yeah.

137
00:13:51.372 --> 00:13:52.999
It's Jim Dear.

138
00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:55.418
Please excuse me.

139
00:13:59.297 --> 00:14:00.923
Hello, there, Lady.

140
00:14:01.674 --> 00:14:03.509
Come on, beat you home.

141
00:14:10.058 --> 00:14:11.726
You win again.

142
00:14:11.893 --> 00:14:13.102
Steady, now.

143
00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:15.021
Steady.

144
00:14:15.563 --> 00:14:17.315
Well, what have we here?

145
00:14:18.816 --> 00:14:20.193
Big girl now, huh?

146
00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:21.361
All right.

147
00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:24.113
Ladies first.

148
00:14:30.078 --> 00:14:31.954
You know, darling, with Lady here,

149
00:14:32.121 --> 00:14:34.749
I'd say life is quite complete.

150
00:14:34.916 --> 00:14:36.084
Yes, dear.

151
00:14:36.250 --> 00:14:40.004
I don't imagine anything could
ever take her place in our hearts.

152
00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:26.759
What a day!

153
00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:30.054
Well, now to dig up some breakfast.

154
00:15:42.984 --> 00:15:45.319
Cute little rascals.

155
00:15:50.575 --> 00:15:53.661
Now. That breakfast, let's see.

156
00:15:54.412 --> 00:15:55.538
Bernie's?

157
00:15:57.165 --> 00:15:59.750
No. Francois...

158
00:15:59.917 --> 00:16:01.210
No, no.

159
00:16:01.377 --> 00:16:03.004
Nope. Too much starch.

160
00:16:03.796 --> 00:16:05.882
Tony's. Oh, that's it.

161
00:16:07.091 --> 00:16:08.718
I haven't been there in a week.

162
00:16:10.094 --> 00:16:12.763
<i>A beautiful day to make pizza</i>

163
00:16:12.930 --> 00:16:17.101
<i>Hey, still we call it Bella notte</i>

164
00:16:18.936 --> 00:16:21.939
Well, <i>buon giorno,</i> Butch.

165
00:16:22.106 --> 00:16:24.484
You want-a your breakfast?

166
00:16:24.650 --> 00:16:28.613
OK. The boss, he's a-saving
some a-nice bones for you.

167
00:16:29.322 --> 00:16:32.158
Breakfast comin' up from a-left field.

168
00:16:33.367 --> 00:16:34.785
Good catch!

169
00:16:41.042 --> 00:16:42.668
Whoa, boy, whoa.

170
00:17:18.746 --> 00:17:19.747
Hey.

171
00:17:22.833 --> 00:17:24.043
Blimey.

172
00:17:24.210 --> 00:17:26.420
Look, Peg, it's the tramp.

173
00:17:27.338 --> 00:17:30.174
Hiya, handsome.
Come to join the party?

174
00:17:30.341 --> 00:17:32.468
All right, all right.
No time for wisecracks.

175
00:17:32.635 --> 00:17:34.053
I've got to get you out.

176
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:37.473
I'm telling you, the pressure's
really on. Signs all over town.

177
00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:41.352
- Gee, thanks.
- You're a bit of all right, chum.

178
00:17:41.519 --> 00:17:44.438
- OK, OK, get going.
- Hey! What's going on over there?

179
00:17:44.605 --> 00:17:47.441
Scram. And be careful.

180
00:17:49.193 --> 00:17:50.444
Why, you mangy mutt.

181
00:17:50.611 --> 00:17:52.613
Hey. Let go. Let go of me.

182
00:18:12.717 --> 00:18:15.344
Well. Snob hill!

183
00:18:19.056 --> 00:18:21.225
Hi, gals. How's pickings?

184
00:18:23.019 --> 00:18:24.770
Pretty slim?

185
00:18:24.937 --> 00:18:28.608
Yeah. I'll bet they've got
a lid on every trash can.

186
00:18:30.234 --> 00:18:32.570
And a fence around every tree.

187
00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:38.784
I wonder what the leash and collar set
does for excitement.

188
00:18:45.166 --> 00:18:46.959
Lassie. Lassie!

189
00:18:48.085 --> 00:18:51.339
Miss Lady, ma'am.

190
00:18:52.256 --> 00:18:56.010
Miss Lady!

191
00:18:56.177 --> 00:18:58.012
Good morning, lassie.

192
00:18:58.179 --> 00:19:00.598
'Tis a bonnie, braw, bright day...

193
00:19:01.557 --> 00:19:02.808
...day.

194
00:19:02.975 --> 00:19:05.227
Why, Miss Lady.

195
00:19:05.394 --> 00:19:07.188
Is something wrong?

196
00:19:07.355 --> 00:19:08.898
Aye. Tell us, lassie.

197
00:19:09.065 --> 00:19:12.318
- If somebody's been mistreatin' ya...
- No, Jock.

198
00:19:12.485 --> 00:19:15.363
It's something I've done, I guess.

199
00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:17.114
You?

200
00:19:17.281 --> 00:19:18.783
It must be.

201
00:19:18.949 --> 00:19:22.411
Jim Dear and Darling are acting so...

202
00:19:26.290 --> 00:19:30.586
- Jim Dear and Darling?
- Hush, lad.

203
00:19:39.679 --> 00:19:43.099
Now, lassie,
get on with the details.

204
00:19:43.265 --> 00:19:45.643
Well, I first noticed it

205
00:19:45.810 --> 00:19:48.521
the other day
when Jim Dear came home.

206
00:19:59.532 --> 00:20:00.700
Down, Lady, down!

207
00:20:05.830 --> 00:20:07.832
Darling, darling!

208
00:20:07.998 --> 00:20:09.417
Are you all right?

209
00:20:09.583 --> 00:20:12.086
Of course I am.
Why shouldn't I be?

210
00:20:17.675 --> 00:20:19.677
I just can't help worrying.

211
00:20:19.844 --> 00:20:21.679
After all, in your condition,

212
00:20:21.846 --> 00:20:23.097
alone here all day,

213
00:20:23.264 --> 00:20:25.433
and walking that dog...

214
00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:29.186
- That dog!
- That dog?

215
00:20:29.353 --> 00:20:31.856
He's never called me that before.

216
00:20:32.022 --> 00:20:33.816
Well, now, lassie,

217
00:20:33.983 --> 00:20:36.444
I wouldn't worry
my wee head about that.

218
00:20:36.610 --> 00:20:39.447
Remember,
they're only humans, after all.

219
00:20:39.613 --> 00:20:41.907
That's right, Miss Lady.

220
00:20:42.074 --> 00:20:46.078
As my grandpappy,
Old Reliable, used to say...

221
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:49.874
I don't recollect if I've ever
mentioned Old Reliable before.

222
00:20:50.040 --> 00:20:53.127
Aye, you have, laddie.

223
00:20:53.294 --> 00:20:55.671
- Frequently.
- Yeah.

224
00:20:55.838 --> 00:20:58.507
But now Darling is... Well...

225
00:20:58.674 --> 00:21:02.011
We've always enjoyed
our afternoon romp together.

226
00:21:02.178 --> 00:21:03.429
But yesterday...

227
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:22.281
No, Lady. No walk today.

228
00:21:32.666 --> 00:21:33.918
No, Lady.

229
00:21:34.668 --> 00:21:35.711
Not now.

230
00:21:37.797 --> 00:21:38.923
Lady!

231
00:21:39.507 --> 00:21:40.925
Drop that, Lady.

232
00:21:41.926 --> 00:21:43.594
Drop it, I say.

233
00:21:45.596 --> 00:21:47.807
It didn't hurt, really.

234
00:21:47.973 --> 00:21:51.393
But Darling has never
struck me... before.

235
00:21:53.771 --> 00:21:55.147
Now, lassie.

236
00:21:55.314 --> 00:21:57.358
Do not take it too seriously.

237
00:21:57.525 --> 00:21:59.568
After all, at a time like this...

238
00:21:59.735 --> 00:22:03.030
Why, yes, you see, Miss Lady,

239
00:22:03.197 --> 00:22:07.618
there comes a time
in the life of all humans when...

240
00:22:08.410 --> 00:22:11.622
Well, as they put it...

241
00:22:11.789 --> 00:22:14.083
Birds and the bees?

242
00:22:14.250 --> 00:22:16.460
Or... Well...

243
00:22:16.627 --> 00:22:19.922
The stork? You <i>know...</i> No?

244
00:22:20.089 --> 00:22:23.050
- Well...
- What he's trying to say, lassie,

245
00:22:23.217 --> 00:22:26.762
is Darling is expecting a wee bairn.

246
00:22:26.929 --> 00:22:28.097
Bairn?

247
00:22:28.264 --> 00:22:31.141
He means a baby, Miss Lady.

248
00:22:31.308 --> 00:22:32.893
Oh.

249
00:22:33.686 --> 00:22:35.729
What's a baby?

250
00:22:35.896 --> 00:22:38.524
Well, they resemble humans.

251
00:22:38.691 --> 00:22:41.777
But I'd say a mite smaller.

252
00:22:41.944 --> 00:22:44.113
Aye. And they walk on all fours.

253
00:22:44.280 --> 00:22:48.367
And if I remember correctly,
they bellow a lot.

254
00:22:48.534 --> 00:22:51.161
Aye. And they're very expensive.

255
00:22:51.912 --> 00:22:53.664
You will not be permitted
to play with it.

256
00:22:53.831 --> 00:22:56.250
But they're mighty sweet.

257
00:22:56.417 --> 00:22:59.128
And very, very soft.

258
00:22:59.295 --> 00:23:01.505
Just a cute little bundle.

259
00:23:02.548 --> 00:23:03.632
Of trouble.

260
00:23:03.966 --> 00:23:06.468
Yeah. They scratch, pinch, pull ears...

261
00:23:07.261 --> 00:23:09.889
But shucks. Any dog can take that.

262
00:23:10.055 --> 00:23:12.141
It's what they do to your happy home.

263
00:23:12.308 --> 00:23:13.684
Move it over, will you, friend?

264
00:23:13.851 --> 00:23:15.561
