00:29:22.719 --> 00:29:27.266
<i>Oh, my little stars wee per</i>

349
00:29:27.432 --> 00:29:31.270
<i>I'll sweep the stardust</i>

350
00:29:31.436 --> 00:29:33.897
<i>For you</i>

351
00:29:39.778 --> 00:29:44.283
<i>Little soft fluffy sleeper</i>

352
00:29:44.449 --> 00:29:48.870
<i>Here comes a pink cloud</i>

353
00:29:49.037 --> 00:29:51.540
<i>For you</i>

354
00:29:58.046 --> 00:30:02.968
<i>Little wandering angel</i>

355
00:30:03.135 --> 00:30:06.471
<i>Fold up your wings</i>

356
00:30:06.638 --> 00:30:10.100
<i>Close your eyes</i>

357
00:30:15.605 --> 00:30:20.402
<i>And may love be your keeper</i>

358
00:30:34.041 --> 00:30:35.459
There, now.

359
00:30:35.625 --> 00:30:37.669
Little star sweeper.

360
00:30:37.836 --> 00:30:39.296
Dream on.

361
00:30:53.185 --> 00:30:55.103
Well, that should do it.

362
00:30:55.937 --> 00:30:58.398
We've got enough here
to take us halfway to China.

363
00:31:03.236 --> 00:31:06.198
Darling. Darling!

364
00:31:06.365 --> 00:31:08.283
We haven't much time.

365
00:31:08.450 --> 00:31:10.660
Jim, I just can't leave him.

366
00:31:10.827 --> 00:31:12.913
He's still so small and helpless.

367
00:31:13.080 --> 00:31:14.748
He'll be all right.

368
00:31:14.915 --> 00:31:18.585
Now come on. If he wakes up,
we'll never get away.

369
00:31:18.752 --> 00:31:20.962
Jim, I feel so guilty
deserting him like this.

370
00:31:21.129 --> 00:31:22.923
Nonsense.

371
00:31:25.175 --> 00:31:28.011
Hey. What's the matter with Lady?

372
00:31:28.178 --> 00:31:30.889
She thinks we're running out on him.

373
00:31:32.057 --> 00:31:33.350
Don't worry, old girl.

374
00:31:33.517 --> 00:31:35.769
We'll be back in a few days.

375
00:31:35.936 --> 00:31:37.270
And Aunt Sarah will be here.

376
00:31:37.437 --> 00:31:39.898
With you here to help her...

377
00:31:40.065 --> 00:31:41.691
There's the old girl now.

378
00:31:42.692 --> 00:31:45.612
Coming, Aunt Sarah. Coming!

379
00:31:45.779 --> 00:31:48.657
Sorry I'm late, dears.
Hope I haven't kept you waiting.

380
00:31:48.824 --> 00:31:50.534
- Let me take your things.
- No.

381
00:31:50.700 --> 00:31:53.078
No fussing. I know my way around.

382
00:31:53.245 --> 00:31:55.330
On your way.
Mustn't miss your train.

383
00:31:55.497 --> 00:31:58.125
Have a good time,
and don't worry about a thing.

384
00:31:58.291 --> 00:32:00.043
Goodbye, dears. Goodbye.

385
00:32:00.210 --> 00:32:02.337
Goodbye.

386
00:32:02.504 --> 00:32:05.215
Now to see that big nephew of mine.

387
00:32:17.227 --> 00:32:19.438
You adorable little...

388
00:32:19.604 --> 00:32:21.857
Good gracious!
What are you doing here?

389
00:32:22.023 --> 00:32:24.734
Go on, now. Shoo, shoo.
Scat. Get out of here.

390
00:32:26.027 --> 00:32:27.362
There, there.

391
00:32:27.529 --> 00:32:31.491
Aunt Sarah won't let
that dog frighten you any more.

392
00:32:31.658 --> 00:32:34.286
No, no, no.

393
00:32:36.830 --> 00:32:42.419
<i>Rock-a-bye baby on the treetop</i>

394
00:32:42.586 --> 00:32:44.880
<i>When the wind blows</i>

395
00:33:16.203 --> 00:33:20.040
<i>We are Siamese if you please</i>

396
00:33:21.625 --> 00:33:26.880
<i>We are Siamese if you don't please</i>

397
00:33:27.047 --> 00:33:32.219
<i>Now we looking over our new domicile</i>

398
00:33:32.385 --> 00:33:36.264
<i>If we like we stay
for maybe quite a while</i>

399
00:33:48.527 --> 00:33:52.697
Do you seeing that thing
swimming round and round?

400
00:33:52.864 --> 00:33:54.199
Yes.

401
00:33:54.908 --> 00:33:58.078
Maybe we could reaching in
and make it drown.

402
00:34:00.121 --> 00:34:03.166
If we sneaking up upon it carefully...

403
00:34:04.834 --> 00:34:07.045
<i>There will be a head for you</i>

404
00:34:07.212 --> 00:34:09.256
<i>A tail for me</i>

405
00:34:32.404 --> 00:34:34.447
Do you hear what I hear?

406
00:34:35.448 --> 00:34:37.659
A baby cry.

407
00:34:37.826 --> 00:34:41.371
<i>Where we finding baby
there are milk nearby</i>

408
00:34:42.789 --> 00:34:46.501
<i>If we look in baby buggy
there could be</i>

