<i>But I love him</i>

776
00:59:06.126 --> 00:59:09.671
<i>Yes, even I have got it pretty bad</i>

777
00:59:10.922 --> 00:59:13.258
<i>You can never tell</i>

778
00:59:13.425 --> 00:59:15.385
<i>When he'll show up</i>

779
00:59:16.386 --> 00:59:18.972
<i>He gives you plenty of trouble</i>

780
00:59:20.599 --> 00:59:24.561
<i>I guess he's just a no 'count pup</i>

781
00:59:24.728 --> 00:59:28.231
<i>But I wish that he were double</i>

782
00:59:28.398 --> 00:59:30.358
<i>He's a tramp</i>

783
00:59:30.525 --> 00:59:32.986
<i>He's a rover</i>

784
00:59:33.153 --> 00:59:36.031
<i>And there's nothin' more to say</i>

785
00:59:37.157 --> 00:59:39.242
<i>If he's a tramp</i>

786
00:59:39.409 --> 00:59:41.161
<i>He's a good one</i>

787
00:59:41.328 --> 00:59:46.708
<i>And I wish that I could travel his way</i>

788
00:59:46.875 --> 00:59:51.254
<i>Wish that I could travel his way</i>

789
00:59:51.421 --> 00:59:56.718
<i>Wish that I could travel his way</i>

790
00:59:58.428 --> 00:59:59.429
Yeah.

791
00:59:59.596 --> 01:00:01.264
But he never takes them serious.

792
01:00:01.932 --> 01:00:06.812
But someday he is meeting
someone different.

793
01:00:06.978 --> 01:00:09.648
Some delicate, fragile creature

794
01:00:09.815 --> 01:00:13.193
who's giving him a wish
to shelter and protect.

795
01:00:13.360 --> 01:00:16.780
Like Miss Park Avenue here, matey?

796
01:00:16.947 --> 01:00:18.907
Could be.

797
01:00:19.074 --> 01:00:22.369
- But when he does...
- Yeah. I'm way ahead of ya.

798
01:00:22.536 --> 01:00:25.038
Under the spell of true love...

799
01:00:25.205 --> 01:00:27.666
The poor chump grows careless...

800
01:00:27.833 --> 01:00:29.709
The Cossacks are picking him up...

801
01:00:29.876 --> 01:00:32.420
And it's curtains for the Tramp.

802
01:00:35.090 --> 01:00:36.758
It's the little cooker, Bill.

803
01:00:36.925 --> 01:00:39.594
- In number four.
- OK.

804
01:00:41.096 --> 01:00:42.472
All right, baby.

805
01:00:42.639 --> 01:00:45.225
They've come to take you home.

806
01:00:45.392 --> 01:00:48.395
You're too nice a girl
to be in this place.

807
01:00:58.947 --> 01:01:00.198
Courage, man.

808
01:01:00.365 --> 01:01:01.575
Courage!

809
01:01:01.741 --> 01:01:02.868
But...

810
01:01:03.034 --> 01:01:06.037
I've never even considered matrimony.

811
01:01:06.204 --> 01:01:08.081
Nor I.

812
01:01:08.248 --> 01:01:10.709
But no matter which of us she accepts,

813
01:01:10.876 --> 01:01:13.587
we'll always be the best of friends.

814
01:01:14.921 --> 01:01:16.089
Now remember,

815
01:01:16.256 --> 01:01:19.217
not a word about her
unfortunate experience.

816
01:01:19.384 --> 01:01:22.971
- We don't want to hurt her feelings.
- Yeah. Yeah.

817
01:01:23.930 --> 01:01:25.599
Lassie.

818
01:01:25.765 --> 01:01:28.852
Miss Lady, ma'am.

819
01:01:29.019 --> 01:01:32.063
Please, I don't want to see anybody.

820
01:01:32.230 --> 01:01:34.691
Now, now, lassie.

821
01:01:34.858 --> 01:01:36.359
Don't feel that way about it.

822
01:01:36.526 --> 01:01:39.112
Of course not, Miss Lady.

823
01:01:39.279 --> 01:01:42.699
Why, some of the finest people
I ever tracked down

824
01:01:42.866 --> 01:01:44.409
- were jailbirds.
- Quiet!

825
01:01:44.576 --> 01:01:46.286
You great loony!

826
01:01:47.245 --> 01:01:49.456
Please, lassie.

827
01:01:49.623 --> 01:01:53.084
We've come with a proposition
for helpin' ya.

828
01:01:53.251 --> 01:01:55.587
Help me? What do you mean?

829
01:01:55.754 --> 01:01:57.672
Well, now...

830
01:01:57.839 --> 01:01:59.716
You see, lassie...

831
01:01:59.883 --> 01:02:02.219
Neither of us is as young
as we used to be.

832
01:02:02.385 --> 01:02:05.222
But we're still in the prime of life.

833
01:02:05.388 --> 01:02:06.389
Aye.

834
01:02:06.556 --> 01:02:10.060
And we've both got
very comfortable homes.

835
01:02:10.227 --> 01:02:12.896
That's right. Where we know

836
01:02:13.063 --> 01:02:16.233
you'll be welcome
and appreciated, Miss Lady.

837
01:02:16.399 --> 01:02:20.987
So... So, to come
directly to the point...

838
01:02:21.154 --> 01:02:22.989
If you could...

839
01:02:23.156 --> 01:02:26.868
...find it possible to...

840
01:02:27.035 --> 01:02:28.161
To...

841
01:02:28.328 --> 01:02:31.748
You're both very kind,
and I do appreciate it.

842
01:02:31.915 --> 01:02:33.833
- But...
- Oh, Pigeon.

843
01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:35.877
Oh, Pi...

844
01:02:36.044 --> 01:02:37.963
Oh! Hi, boys.

845
01:02:41.633 --> 01:02:43.718
Anything new in the kennel club set?

846
01:02:48.139 --> 01:02:50.725
A little something
I picked up for you, Pige.

847
01:03:00.277 --> 01:03:02.362
Looks like I'm the one
that's in the doghouse.

848
01:03:02.529 --> 01:03:06.992
If this person is
annoying you, Miss Lady...

849
01:03:07.158 --> 01:03:09.995
We'll gladly throw the rascal out.

850
01:03:10.161 --> 01:03:12.664
That won't be necessary. Thank you.

851
01:03:12.831 --> 01:03:15.000
Very well, ma'am.

852
01:03:15.166 --> 01:03:17.961
You... You...

853
01:03:18.128 --> 01:03:20.213
...mongrel!

854
01:03:24.926 --> 01:03:27.512
Come on, Pige.

855
01:03:27.679 --> 01:03:29.973
It wasn't my fault.

856
01:03:31.349 --> 01:03:34.811
I thought you were
right behind me. Honest.

857
01:03:34.978 --> 01:03:37.230
When I heard they'd
taken you to the pound...

858
01:03:37.397 --> 01:03:39.691
Don't even mention that horrible place.

859
01:03:39.858 --> 01:03:42.861
I was so embarrassed and...

860
01:03:43.028 --> 01:03:46.072
- And frightened.
- Now, now.

861
01:03:46.239 --> 01:03:50.035
Who could ever harm
a cute little trick like you?

862
01:03:50.201 --> 01:03:52.245
Trick? Trick!

863
01:03:52.412 --> 01:03:56.207
- That reminds me, who is Trixie?
- Trixie?

864
01:03:56.374 --> 01:03:59.002
And Lulu and Fifi
and Rosita Chiquita wh...

865
01:03:59.169 --> 01:04:01.212
- Whatever her name is.
- Chiquita...

866
01:04:01.379 --> 01:04:03.298
Oh! Yes! Well, I-I...

867
01:04:03.465 --> 01:04:06.801
As far as I'm concerned,
you needn't worry about your old heel.

868
01:04:06.968 --> 01:04:07.969
My heel?

869
01:04:08.136 --> 01:04:10.221
I don't need you
to shelter and protect me.

870
01:04:10.388 --> 01:04:12.849
- But...
- If you grow careless, don't blame me.

871
01:04:13.016 --> 01:04:16.686
I don't care if the Cossacks
do pick you up! Goodbye.

872
01:04:17.562 --> 01:04:19.230
And take this with you.

873
01:05:26.506 --> 01:05:28.508
Stop that.

874
01:05:31.719 --> 01:05:33.430
Hush, now, hush.

875
01:05:37.725 --> 01:05:39.394
Stop that racket!

876
01:05:42.021 --> 01:05:43.148
What's wrong, Pige?

877
01:05:43.314 --> 01:05:44.983
- A rat!
- Where?

878
01:05:45.150 --> 01:05:47.318
Upstairs, in the baby's room!

879
01:05:47.485 --> 01:05:50.155
- How do I get in?
- The little door.

880
01:05:50.321 --> 01:05:51.614
On the porch.

881
01:07:37.929 --> 01:07:39.347
Merciful heavens!

882
01:07:39.514 --> 01:07:43.101
Oh, you poor little darling.

883
01:07:43.268 --> 01:07:46.187
No, no, no.
Thank goodness you're not hurt.

884
01:07:46.354 --> 01:07:49.232
You... You vicious brutes. Back!

885
01:07:49.399 --> 01:07:50.942
Get back!

886
01:07:51.109 --> 01:07:53.319
Go on! Get back!

887
01:07:53.486 --> 01:07:57.365
The pound. The pound, that's it.
I'll call the pound.

888
01:07:59.659 --> 01:08:02.078
Come here, you. Come here!

889
01:08:03.162 --> 01:08:04.497
Come on, come on.

890
01:08:04.664 --> 01:08:06.708
Come along. I'll call them this minute.

891
01:08:06.874 --> 01:08:09.419
I won't sleep a wink
with that brute in the house.

892
01:08:17.302 --> 01:08:19.971
Hello? Hello!

893
01:08:24.142 --> 01:08:27.186
I don't care if you
are alone there, young man.

894
01:08:27.353 --> 01:08:30.398
I insist you pick him up immediately.

895
01:08:38.281 --> 01:08:40.408
Darling, look.

896
01:08:42.035 --> 01:08:45.622
If you want my advice
you'll destroy that animal at once.

897
01:08:45.788 --> 01:08:47.332
Don't worry, ma'am.

898
01:08:47.790 --> 01:08:50.001
We've been after this one for months.

899
01:08:50.168 --> 01:08:51.961
We'll take care of him.

900
01:08:55.840 --> 01:08:57.884
- What do you suppose...?
- Say, what's going on here?

901
01:08:58.051 --> 01:08:59.844
Just picking up a stray, mister.

902
01:09:00.011 --> 01:09:02.263
Come on, giddap.

903
01:09:02.430 --> 01:09:03.765
Caught him attacking a baby.

904
01:09:03.931 --> 01:09:05.224
- Good heavens.
- My baby.

905
01:09:05.391 --> 01:09:06.476
Aunt Sarah!

906
01:09:06.643 --> 01:09:07.644
Aunt Sarah!

907
01:09:09.270 --> 01:09:10.688
Aunt Sarah!

908
01:09:12.690 --> 01:09:14.609
I was certain he was no good

909
01:09:14.776 --> 01:09:17.028
the moment I first laid eyes on him.

910
01:09:17.195 --> 01:09:19.739
Yeah, but...

911
01:09:19.906 --> 01:09:23.159
I never thought
he'd do a thing like that.

912
01:09:24.577 --> 01:09:26.746
Thank goodness I got there in time.
There they were...

913
01:09:26.913 --> 01:09:30.041
No, I'm sure there must be
some mistake. Lady wouldn't...

914
01:09:32.293 --> 01:09:35.046
Watch out! That dog's loose.
Keep her away.

915
01:09:35.213 --> 01:09:37.674
Nonsense.
She's trying to tell us something.

916
01:09:38.841 --> 01:09:40.134
What is it, old girl?

917
01:09:41.928 --> 01:09:43.096
What are you try...

918
01:09:43.262 --> 01:09:44.931
Darling, Aunt Sarah, come here.

919
01:09:45.098 --> 01:09:46.641
What is it, Jim?

920
01:09:47.266 --> 01:09:48.267
A rat!

921
01:09:48.434 --> 01:09:50.103
A rat?

922
01:09:50.269 --> 01:09:52.021
We should've known.

923
01:09:52.188 --> 01:09:55.233
I misjudged him.

924
01:09:55.400 --> 01:09:56.401
Badly.

925
01:09:56.567 --> 01:10:00.029
Come on. We got to stop that wagon.

926
01:10:00.196 --> 01:10:03.533
But, man, we don't know
which way they've gone.

927
01:10:04.033 --> 01:10:05.910
We'll track 'em down.

928
01:10:06.077 --> 01:10:07.245
And then?

929
01:10:07.412 --> 01:10:08.996
We'll hold 'em.

930
01:10:09.163 --> 01:10:11.040
Hold 'em at bay.

931
01:10:23.386 --> 01:10:24.470
Now what?

932
01:10:24.637 --> 01:10:27.807
The scent. Follow the scent.

933
01:10:34.689 --> 01:10:36.858
Let's face it, man.

934
01:10:37.024 --> 01:10:39.736
We both know you've lost
your sense of smell.

935
01:11:46.177 --> 01:11:47.637
Go on, get out of here.

936
01:11:48.387 --> 01:11:49.472
Go on, get away.

937
01:11:55.186 --> 01:11:56.896
Easy. Go on, get away.

938
01:11:57.063 --> 01:11:58.689
Watch it now. Watch it!

939
01:12:13.454 --> 01:12:14.872
Hi, Pige.

940
01:12:45.778 --> 01:12:48.698
All right, everybody, watch the birdy.

941
01:12:59.917 --> 01:13:01.043
Steady, now.

942
01:13:02.795 --> 01:13:04.130
Hold it.

943
01:13:07.717 --> 01:13:09.719
I guess I used a little too much.

944
01:13:12.680 --> 01:13:15.182
Darling, visitors.

945
01:13:15.349 --> 01:13:16.434
Visitors?

946
01:13:17.393 --> 01:13:19.395
Why, it's Jock.

947
01:13:21.022 --> 01:13:22.982
And good old Trusty.

948
01:13:23.774 --> 01:13:25.192
Careful now, man.

949
01:13:25.359 --> 01:13:28.237
Careful. It's a wee bit slippery.

950
01:13:28.529 --> 01:13:30.072
Yes, yes.

951
01:13:32.158 --> 01:13:34.452
All right, boy. We'll let 'em in.

952
01:13:35.745 --> 01:13:37.747
No, no, not you, young man.

953
01:13:37.914 --> 01:13:39.206
You're going to take a nap.

954
01:13:39.749 --> 01:13:41.709
Well, Merry Christmas.

955
01:13:41.876 --> 01:13:44.211
Come in. If you'll just
step into the parlour,

956
01:13:44.378 --> 01:13:46.172
I'll see about refreshments.

957
01:13:46.339 --> 01:13:49.800
Darling, where did you
put the dog biscuits?

958
01:13:49.967 --> 01:13:52.345
The box Aunt Sarah sent for Christmas.

959
01:13:52.511 --> 01:13:53.971
In the kitchen, Jim, dear.

960
01:13:54.805 --> 01:13:56.724
No doubt about it.

961
01:13:56.891 --> 01:13:59.352
They've got their mother's eyes.

962
01:14:01.228 --> 01:14:02.521
Aye.

963
01:14:05.441 --> 01:14:07.902
But there's a bit of
their father in them too.

964
01:14:09.946 --> 01:14:13.866
Well, and I see you finally
acquired a collar.

965
01:14:14.033 --> 01:14:17.078
Oh. Yes.

966
01:14:17.244 --> 01:14:18.537
Complete with Licence.

967
01:14:18.704 --> 01:14:21.791
Oh, yeah, a new collar.

968
01:14:21.958 --> 01:14:24.835
Caught the scent the moment
I came in the house.

969
01:14:25.670 --> 01:14:27.046
Trusty, I says,

970
01:14:27.213 --> 01:14:31.217
Trusty, somebody's
wearing a new collar.

971
01:14:32.218 --> 01:14:35.638
'Course, my sense of smell

972
01:14:35.805 --> 01:14:38.182
is very highly developed.

973
01:14:38.349 --> 01:14:39.976
Runs in the family, you know.

974
01:14:40.142 --> 01:14:42.561
There'll be no livin'
with him from now on.

975
01:14:42.728 --> 01:14:47.316
As my grandpappy,
Old Reliable, used to say...

976
01:14:47.483 --> 01:14:51.529
I don't recollect if I've ever
mentioned Old Reliable before.

977
01:14:51.696 --> 01:14:53.823
No, you haven't, Uncle Trusty.

978
01:14:55.533 --> 01:14:57.660
I haven't?

979
01:14:57.827 --> 01:14:59.787
Well...

980
01:14:59.954 --> 01:15:03.374
As Old Reliable used to say...

981
01:15:03.541 --> 01:15:04.959
He'd say...

982
01:15:06.252 --> 01:15:08.337
He'd say...

983
01:15:12.758 --> 01:15:15.386
Doggone.

984
01:15:15.553 --> 01:15:17.722
You know,

985
01:15:17.888 --> 01:15:21.475
I clean forgot what it was
he used to say.

986
01:15:26.313 --> 01:15:30.860
<i>Peace, my children</i>

987
01:15:31.027 --> 01:15:36.032
<i>Of good will</i>

988
01:15:36.198 --> 01:15:39.493
<i>Peace, my children</i>

989
01:15:39.660 --> 01:15:41.662
<i>Peace</i>

990
01:15:41.829 --> 01:15:44.707
<i>Be</i>

991
01:15:44.874 --> 01:15:48.753
<i>Still</i>

